explanation.rules:
In the first syllable: a [Ea], á [ɔa], e [e:], ei [ai], ey [Ei], i [i:], o [o:], oy [ɔi], ó [ɔu], u [u:], ú [Uu], ø [ø:]
Between vowels: ð = g. The first applicable rule is applied:  
1. ð/g [w] | [u(:)] —;
2. ð/g [j] | [i(:)] — or — [i(:)];
3. ð/g [v] | — [u(:)];
4. ð/g [v] in a noun, [Ø] in a verb.
